    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Artists who etch, by hand, metal plates to be used in creating etchings, which are prints made by an intaglio process in which the design is worked into an acid-resistant substance coating the metal printing plate, and the plate is then dipped in acid to form the design.</Note_Text>
